The paper deals with predictive process monitoring, which involves analyzing events produced during the execution of a business process to predict the final outcome of an ongoing case. This is a machine learning task, and the paper evaluates existing methods with respect to both accuracy and temporal stability. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with classification tasks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DB (Databases).
